WEBVTT

00:00:34.899 --> 00:00:38.479
Life is so unpredictable.

00:00:38.479 --> 00:00:41.479
Looking back, I never thought I'd be here.

00:00:43.479 --> 00:00:46.280
Still, I don't regret the choices I've made.

00:00:47.979 --> 00:00:53.189
Although at times, I wasn't sure where they'd date me.

00:00:53.189 --> 00:00:54.990
Hey Liz.

00:00:54.990 --> 00:00:55.789
Hey, Zach.

00:00:55.789 --> 00:00:57.189
What are you doing here?

00:00:57.189 --> 00:01:00.090
I was just head and work.

00:01:00.090 --> 00:01:01.990
I was friendly though.

00:01:01.990 --> 00:01:04.489
I actually used to have a 15-minute.

00:01:04.489 --> 00:01:04.989
Hey, Meg.

00:01:04.989 --> 00:01:05.689
Hey.

00:01:05.689 --> 00:01:06.890
You guys both work here?

00:01:06.890 --> 00:01:07.790
Yes, we do.

00:01:07.790 --> 00:01:08.290
Nice.

00:01:08.290 --> 00:01:08.790
Yes.

00:01:08.790 --> 00:01:11.489
Listen, if you have a couple of minutes,

00:01:11.489 --> 00:01:13.189
can I buy you something to drink?

00:01:13.189 --> 00:01:14.189
My treat.

00:01:14.189 --> 00:01:15.489
Anything?

00:01:15.489 --> 00:01:18.739
Uh, um.

00:01:18.739 --> 00:01:23.340
Well, okay.

00:01:23.340 --> 00:01:25.340
One Earl Grey coming up.

00:01:25.340 --> 00:01:26.340
Thank you very much.

00:01:26.340 --> 00:01:28.540
Chino with whipped cream.

00:01:28.540 --> 00:01:30.540
That sounds so much better.

00:01:30.540 --> 00:01:31.739
Uh, cheese.

00:01:31.739 --> 00:01:32.939
What I want.

00:01:32.939 --> 00:01:38.239
How do you work at a coffee shop and drink tea?

00:01:38.239 --> 00:01:41.540
I just needed an after-school job.

00:01:41.540 --> 00:01:44.640
Meg had mentioned there was an opening here and I figured

00:01:44.640 --> 00:01:47.939
it would be great for pioneering once I graduate.

00:01:47.939 --> 00:01:48.739
Pioneering?

00:01:48.739 --> 00:01:49.340
Yeah.

00:01:49.340 --> 00:01:52.640
I didn't realize that's what you were planning on doing.

00:01:52.640 --> 00:01:54.939
How many times do we run into each other?

00:01:54.939 --> 00:01:56.939
Whether it's school or at the King of Hall?

00:01:56.939 --> 00:01:59.439
And this is the first time that we've actually

00:01:59.439 --> 00:02:00.640
getting a chance to talk.

00:02:00.640 --> 00:02:01.340
Yeah.

00:02:01.340 --> 00:02:02.340
I know.

00:02:02.340 --> 00:02:04.739
I guess that's part of being the new guy, right?

00:02:04.739 --> 00:02:05.340
Oh, come on.

00:02:05.340 --> 00:02:07.040
You're not that new.

00:02:07.040 --> 00:02:07.540
I don't know.

00:02:07.540 --> 00:02:10.340
I guess it still feels like that sometimes.

00:02:10.340 --> 00:02:11.840
Do you not like it here?

00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:13.240
No, it's not that I don't like it.

00:02:13.240 --> 00:02:15.240
It's just...

00:02:15.240 --> 00:02:17.740
It's totally different.

00:02:17.740 --> 00:02:20.139
Why did your family move?

00:02:20.139 --> 00:02:23.340
My dad's opening up a restaurant not too far from here.

00:02:23.340 --> 00:02:27.639
So we moved to be closer.

00:02:27.639 --> 00:02:29.639
I don't have to give him a minute, Dad.

00:02:29.639 --> 00:02:32.639
He's not a witness, so.

00:02:32.639 --> 00:02:36.139
How does he feel about the truth?

00:02:36.139 --> 00:02:40.039
I think his real concern is that I make time

00:02:40.039 --> 00:02:42.439
for the business when I graduate.

00:02:42.439 --> 00:02:44.939
Is that what you want to do?

00:02:44.939 --> 00:02:47.139
In the end, I think I want what most people want.

00:02:47.139 --> 00:02:50.139
I have a job doing something that I like to do.

00:02:50.139 --> 00:02:51.439
Make some money.

00:02:51.439 --> 00:02:52.139
How about you?

00:02:52.139 --> 00:02:54.539
I mean, besides pioneering.

00:02:54.539 --> 00:02:56.539
What plans do you have?

00:02:56.539 --> 00:02:58.639
I've been wanting to take some classes.

00:02:58.639 --> 00:03:00.879
Oh, it's my dad.

00:03:00.879 --> 00:03:02.879
I'm the one sad.

00:03:02.879 --> 00:03:06.610
Hey, Dad.

00:03:06.610 --> 00:03:10.680
Yeah, I can be there in 15.

00:03:10.680 --> 00:03:15.509
Okay.

00:03:15.509 --> 00:03:17.009
I'm sorry.

00:03:17.009 --> 00:03:18.610
So then I let you go.

00:03:18.610 --> 00:03:20.409
My dad needs me at the restaurant.

00:03:20.409 --> 00:03:21.409
Totally understand.

00:03:21.409 --> 00:03:23.409
But I'll definitely see you in school, okay?

00:03:23.409 --> 00:03:24.210
Yes.

00:03:24.210 --> 00:03:25.210
Okay.

00:03:25.210 --> 00:03:26.210
Thank you for my tea.

00:03:26.210 --> 00:03:27.210
You're welcome.

00:03:27.210 --> 00:03:39.319
See you later, Zach.

00:03:39.319 --> 00:03:42.520
Bye.

00:03:42.520 --> 00:03:43.520
I know what that was about.

00:03:43.520 --> 00:03:46.520
I don't know what you're talking about.

00:03:46.520 --> 00:03:47.520
No?

00:03:47.520 --> 00:03:48.520
She's new here.

00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:49.520
Mm-hmm.

00:03:49.520 --> 00:03:50.520
She's talking.

00:03:50.520 --> 00:03:52.520
Oh, she's just trying to be nice.

00:03:52.520 --> 00:03:53.520
Mm-hmm.

00:03:53.520 --> 00:03:54.520
Trying to be nice.

00:03:54.520 --> 00:03:57.439
Got it.

00:03:57.439 --> 00:03:58.439
Fun.

00:03:58.439 --> 00:04:04.370
What?

00:04:04.370 --> 00:04:07.169
It seems like he likes you.

00:04:07.169 --> 00:04:09.569
He seems nice.

00:04:09.569 --> 00:04:13.580
I don't even know him.

00:04:13.580 --> 00:04:15.780
Is it because he's not baptized?

00:04:15.780 --> 00:04:17.379
But he's not baptized?

00:04:17.379 --> 00:04:19.180
I thought you knew that.

00:04:19.180 --> 00:04:21.379
And no, I just zoomed.

00:04:21.379 --> 00:04:23.180
Well, that tells you something.

00:04:23.180 --> 00:04:25.379
He knows it's the truth.

00:04:25.379 --> 00:04:29.579
And again, I can't even consider someone who's not baptized.

00:04:29.579 --> 00:04:34.379
Blaze, not everyone is raising the truth like us.

00:04:34.379 --> 00:04:37.449
Give him a chance.

00:04:37.449 --> 00:05:07.470
Try to be a little more understanding.

00:05:07.470 --> 00:05:10.569
Because everything OK?

00:05:10.569 --> 00:05:11.769
It's been better.

00:05:11.769 --> 00:05:13.569
Why was the coach yelling at you?

00:05:13.569 --> 00:05:15.370
I told him I wasn't playing soccer anymore.

00:05:15.370 --> 00:05:17.370
He just went off.

00:05:17.370 --> 00:05:19.769
They were going to offer me a sports scholarship.

00:05:19.769 --> 00:05:23.370
And now, I'm throwing my future away.

00:05:23.370 --> 00:05:26.370
Scholarship must be good.

00:05:26.370 --> 00:05:28.970
I used to play on the team of my old school.

00:05:28.970 --> 00:05:34.769
But my parents, my mom, she doesn't really

00:05:34.769 --> 00:05:37.170
want me to play anymore.

00:05:37.170 --> 00:05:40.170
Can you tell the coach why you can't play?

00:05:40.170 --> 00:05:41.569
Are you kidding?

00:05:41.569 --> 00:05:44.370
You would never understand the whole religion thing?

00:05:44.370 --> 00:05:48.170
Well, if it's any consolation, I think what you did today

00:05:48.170 --> 00:05:52.259
was the right decision.

00:05:52.259 --> 00:05:54.259
Thanks.

00:05:54.259 --> 00:05:59.660
But between you and me, I really want to play.

00:05:59.660 --> 00:06:02.060
No, I just feel torn sometimes.

00:06:02.060 --> 00:06:03.660
I can understand that.

00:06:03.660 --> 00:06:08.660
But being able to dedicate you to life to Jehovah,

00:06:08.660 --> 00:06:10.459
it's worth any sacrifice.

00:06:10.459 --> 00:06:13.660
You mean like baptism?

00:06:13.660 --> 00:06:16.259
Yeah, you have a date plan?

00:06:16.259 --> 00:06:17.660
You know, with school wrapping up,

00:06:17.660 --> 00:06:20.259
I've just been focused on helping my dad out.

00:06:20.259 --> 00:06:22.860
I'm hoping maybe for the end of the year.

00:06:22.860 --> 00:06:25.259
But we'll see how it goes.

00:06:25.259 --> 00:06:26.860
Well, I think what you did today

00:06:26.860 --> 00:06:31.000
was definitely a step in the right direction.

00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:33.680
Thanks.

00:06:33.680 --> 00:06:35.480
Yeah.

00:06:35.480 --> 00:06:36.879
I should probably go get changed.

00:06:36.879 --> 00:06:37.480
OK.

00:06:37.480 --> 00:06:38.480
I'll see you tonight.

00:06:38.480 --> 00:06:39.879
Tonight?

00:06:39.879 --> 00:06:40.680
At the meeting?

00:06:40.680 --> 00:06:42.079
Oh, there you are.

00:06:42.079 --> 00:06:43.879
Of course.

00:06:43.879 --> 00:06:44.879
Hey, man.

00:06:44.879 --> 00:06:47.079
Oh, am I interrupting something?

00:06:47.079 --> 00:06:49.079
No, I was just leaving.

00:06:49.079 --> 00:06:49.879
I'll see you tonight.

00:06:49.879 --> 00:06:52.509
All right.

00:06:52.509 --> 00:06:55.110
Hey, see you tonight.

00:06:55.110 --> 00:06:55.709
What's that about?

00:06:55.709 --> 00:06:56.709
Our meeting.

00:06:56.709 --> 00:07:00.110
Remember, I told you I'm becoming a Jehovah's Witness.

00:07:00.110 --> 00:07:02.910
I mean, I know you told me, but saying and doing

00:07:02.910 --> 00:07:04.310
two different things, my friend.

00:07:04.310 --> 00:07:05.709
Well, I'm ready to do it.

00:07:05.709 --> 00:07:07.709
Why now?

00:07:07.709 --> 00:07:08.509
No.

00:07:08.509 --> 00:07:10.910
Because a church girl?

00:07:10.910 --> 00:07:11.709
No way.

00:07:11.709 --> 00:07:13.110
I don't think so.

00:07:13.110 --> 00:07:14.509
What's that supposed to mean?

00:07:14.509 --> 00:07:15.509
Come on.

00:07:15.509 --> 00:07:16.910
Nothing against Liz, right?

00:07:16.910 --> 00:07:19.110
But she's really religious.

00:07:19.110 --> 00:07:20.509
You?

00:07:20.509 --> 00:07:22.709
Not so much.

00:07:22.709 --> 00:07:24.110
Is that so?

00:07:24.110 --> 00:07:25.509
I'm just telling you how I see it.

00:07:25.509 --> 00:07:28.509
Well, start seeing it a little differently.

00:07:28.509 --> 00:07:30.110
I mean, if you say so.

00:07:30.110 --> 00:07:32.110
But look, I thought we had plans tonight.

00:07:32.110 --> 00:07:34.110
Well, plans.

00:07:34.110 --> 00:07:36.709
The game at Westbrook Park.

00:07:36.709 --> 00:07:38.509
I have my meeting tonight.

00:07:38.509 --> 00:07:39.910
Look, it's fine.

00:07:39.910 --> 00:07:41.910
I can find someone else, you know?

00:07:41.910 --> 00:07:44.910
I got a bunch of best friends.

00:07:44.910 --> 00:07:45.709
Don't worry about me.

00:07:45.709 --> 00:07:48.709
Stop, stop.

00:07:48.709 --> 00:07:49.509
Count me in.

00:07:49.509 --> 00:07:50.310
I'll be there.

00:07:50.310 --> 00:07:51.310
Yeah?

00:07:51.310 --> 00:07:52.310
Yeah.

00:07:52.310 --> 00:07:52.509
Cool.

00:07:52.509 --> 00:07:54.110
Well, look, I got to go get changed.

00:07:54.110 --> 00:07:55.709
I'll see you tonight.

00:07:55.709 --> 00:08:02.949
I'll see you tonight.

00:08:02.949 --> 00:08:05.149
Liz, I can't make it tonight.

00:08:05.149 --> 00:08:06.550
Thanks for the talk.

00:08:06.550 --> 00:08:08.149
Let's chat tomorrow, OK?

00:08:08.149 --> 00:09:55.230
That sounds good.

00:09:55.230 --> 00:09:56.429
Liz, what do you think about that?

00:09:56.429 --> 00:09:58.830
Is that something you can do?

00:09:58.830 --> 00:10:00.830
Liz?

00:10:00.830 --> 00:10:02.629
Liz, where'd you go?

00:10:02.629 --> 00:10:06.029
You weren't even listening to our conversation, huh?

00:10:06.029 --> 00:10:07.230
I know, I'm sorry.

00:10:07.230 --> 00:10:09.830
Is everything OK?

00:10:09.830 --> 00:10:16.029
Actually, there's something I want to tell you.

00:10:16.029 --> 00:10:18.830
I'm not quite sure how to say it.

00:10:18.830 --> 00:10:23.490
OK, we're listening.

00:10:23.490 --> 00:10:27.059
There's someone I'm interested in.

00:10:27.059 --> 00:10:29.659
Interested in?

00:10:29.659 --> 00:10:32.460
Someone I'd like to date.

00:10:32.460 --> 00:10:34.059
You're only 17.

00:10:34.059 --> 00:10:36.259
I'm turning 18 the next month.

00:10:36.259 --> 00:10:40.889
That's not the point.

00:10:40.889 --> 00:10:42.289
What is the point?

00:10:42.289 --> 00:10:44.889
You know how your mom and I feel about you even

00:10:44.889 --> 00:10:46.889
thinking about dating so young.

00:10:46.889 --> 00:10:49.799
Who are we talking about?

00:10:49.799 --> 00:10:50.799
Zach.

00:10:50.799 --> 00:10:52.000
Zach Tanner?

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:54.000
Dad, if this is about him not being baptized.

00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:58.200
Whoa, yes, this is exactly about him not being baptized.

00:10:58.200 --> 00:11:01.200
And even if he was, you're both still too young.

00:11:01.200 --> 00:11:02.200
We're not that young.

00:11:02.200 --> 00:11:03.600
We're graduating soon.

00:11:03.600 --> 00:11:07.600
Liz, neither one of you is ready for marriage right now.

00:11:07.799 --> 00:11:12.200
Can you honestly see Zach as being your spiritual head?

00:11:12.200 --> 00:11:20.639
I never thought I'd feel like this.

00:11:20.639 --> 00:11:22.240
Liz, we understand.

00:11:22.240 --> 00:11:23.840
We're not against you finding someone

00:11:23.840 --> 00:11:26.639
that's going to make you happy when they were not.

00:11:26.639 --> 00:11:28.039
But the problem is, darling,

00:11:28.039 --> 00:11:31.639
that when you start developing strong feelings for someone

00:11:31.639 --> 00:11:38.519
early on, it is so hard to see their potential flaws.

00:11:38.519 --> 00:11:39.720
But I thought when you're married,

00:11:39.720 --> 00:11:41.919
you're supposed to overlook flaws.

00:11:41.919 --> 00:11:43.720
That's true.

00:11:43.720 --> 00:11:47.720
But the time to keep your eyes open to potential spiritual

00:11:47.720 --> 00:11:53.320
problems is way before marriage, not afterwards.

00:11:53.320 --> 00:11:56.279
I know.

00:11:56.279 --> 00:12:03.279
It's just when I see other girls with their boyfriends.

00:12:03.279 --> 00:12:05.480
I want that too.

00:12:05.480 --> 00:12:08.789
Liz, we understand.

00:12:08.789 --> 00:12:15.590
But Zach hasn't even taken the first step towards baptism yet.

00:12:15.590 --> 00:12:19.190
Neither one of you are ready for dating.

00:12:19.190 --> 00:12:39.289
I'm sorry, but there's no way your mom and I can approve of this.

00:12:39.289 --> 00:12:43.440
I think it's time to warm you up.

00:12:43.440 --> 00:12:44.240
Yeah, man.

00:12:44.240 --> 00:12:51.830
So what's up?

00:12:51.830 --> 00:12:54.830
Well, haven't you been responding to any of my texts?

00:12:54.830 --> 00:12:55.830
I know.

00:12:55.830 --> 00:12:58.830
I'm sorry.

00:12:58.830 --> 00:13:04.279
You remember how you told me you felt

00:13:04.279 --> 00:13:09.879
when a coach wanted you to play, but you knew you couldn't?

00:13:09.879 --> 00:13:11.879
When I told him I felt torn?

00:13:11.879 --> 00:13:12.879
Yeah.

00:13:12.879 --> 00:13:14.879
What does that have to do with?

00:13:14.879 --> 00:13:19.879
My parents feel like we're too young to get into a relationship.

00:13:19.879 --> 00:13:21.279
Your parents, Liz?

00:13:21.279 --> 00:13:23.279
You're almost 18.

00:13:23.279 --> 00:13:26.279
No, I know.

00:13:26.279 --> 00:13:27.679
It's not just that.

00:13:27.679 --> 00:13:29.879
So we had something here.

00:13:29.879 --> 00:13:36.379
Don't let them ruin this for us.

00:13:36.379 --> 00:13:38.779
I feel like I have my goals.

00:13:38.779 --> 00:13:42.379
And I don't think you're on the same page.

00:13:42.379 --> 00:13:44.179
What kind of goals are you talking about?

00:13:44.179 --> 00:13:45.179
I'm hearing.

00:13:45.179 --> 00:13:47.379
Maybe in the future of Angelizer School.

00:13:47.379 --> 00:13:48.379
Oh, come on.

00:13:48.379 --> 00:13:50.379
I'm not opposed to any of that.

00:13:50.379 --> 00:13:53.850
You're not for it, either.

00:13:53.850 --> 00:13:58.450
I admit sometimes I miss meetings, and I should be out in service more.

00:13:58.450 --> 00:13:59.450
I know that.

00:13:59.450 --> 00:14:01.450
But I'll turn things around.

00:14:01.450 --> 00:14:06.200
When?

00:14:06.200 --> 00:14:07.799
That's why I have you.

00:14:07.799 --> 00:14:08.799
You can help me.

00:14:08.799 --> 00:14:13.070
Help me, Zach.

00:14:13.070 --> 00:14:17.210
Come on, Liz.

00:14:17.210 --> 00:14:26.019
You can't.

00:14:26.019 --> 00:14:27.019
Where you won't.

00:14:27.019 --> 00:14:37.159
I was hoping you weren't going to be like this.

00:14:37.159 --> 00:14:38.159
Be like one.

00:14:38.559 --> 00:14:40.559
I know I have things to work on.

00:14:40.559 --> 00:14:43.559
Just allow you to give me a little bit more time before you just write me off.

00:14:43.559 --> 00:14:45.559
I'm not writing you off.

00:14:45.559 --> 00:14:46.759
Really?

00:14:46.759 --> 00:14:51.169
So you're saying you'd give us another chance?

00:14:51.169 --> 00:14:52.169
Exactly.

00:14:52.169 --> 00:14:53.169
You know what, though?

00:14:53.169 --> 00:15:00.730
I can never be with someone that expects perfection.

00:15:00.730 --> 00:15:25.379
Well, neither was this.

00:15:25.379 --> 00:15:26.980
What are you doing here?

00:15:26.980 --> 00:15:29.379
I'm just walking, Jasper.

00:15:29.379 --> 00:15:30.379
What are you doing?

00:15:30.379 --> 00:15:33.379
I'm actually waiting for a shipment for my dad's restaurant, so.

00:15:33.379 --> 00:15:34.179
How nice.

00:15:34.179 --> 00:15:38.279
I'm hoping it's your soon.

00:15:38.279 --> 00:15:40.879
I know we've talked enough, but.

00:15:40.879 --> 00:15:45.879
I don't think I really had a chance to tell you how sorry I am that things didn't work out with you and Liz.

00:15:45.879 --> 00:15:50.000
She really liked you.

00:15:50.000 --> 00:15:52.399
Thanks, I guess.

00:15:52.399 --> 00:15:55.399
You know, maybe things can still work out.

00:15:55.399 --> 00:15:58.399
Yeah, I don't think so.

00:15:58.399 --> 00:16:00.600
To be honest, it's been months now.

00:16:00.600 --> 00:16:02.200
And you know what?

00:16:02.200 --> 00:16:04.399
We just weren't right for each other.

00:16:04.399 --> 00:16:05.600
Really?

00:16:05.600 --> 00:16:06.200
Yeah.

00:16:06.200 --> 00:16:11.399
I mean, she's the type of girl that was expecting me to be perfect.

00:16:11.399 --> 00:16:14.799
And on top of that, she didn't even really know how she fell.

00:16:14.799 --> 00:16:15.600
I know.

00:16:15.600 --> 00:16:18.799
I told her the same thing.

