00:49:52.030 --> 00:49:53.030
Okay.

00:49:53.030 --> 00:49:54.030
Great.

00:49:54.030 --> 00:49:57.030
So, tonight, around seven.

00:49:57.030 --> 00:49:58.030
Okay.

00:49:58.030 --> 00:49:59.030
All right.

00:49:59.030 --> 00:50:00.030
That sounds perfect.

00:50:00.030 --> 00:50:01.030
See you tonight, then.

00:50:01.030 --> 00:50:04.110
Okay.

00:50:04.110 --> 00:50:58.610
Bye.

00:50:58.610 --> 00:50:59.610
Cheers.

00:50:59.610 --> 00:51:00.610
I'd like to introduce to you,

00:51:00.610 --> 00:51:51.739
brother and sister, John and Elizabeth Shaw.

00:51:51.739 --> 00:51:53.739
Leaving?

00:51:53.739 --> 00:51:55.739
Does it matter?

00:51:55.739 --> 00:51:56.739
No.

00:51:56.739 --> 00:51:58.739
Not really.

00:51:58.739 --> 00:52:00.739
I just left some paperwork here.

00:52:00.739 --> 00:52:01.739
I'm working late.

00:52:01.739 --> 00:52:03.739
Of course you are.

00:52:03.739 --> 00:52:04.739
Yeah, well.

00:52:04.739 --> 00:52:06.739
At least I'll get a break from the nagging.

00:52:06.739 --> 00:52:07.739
Yes, Zach.

00:52:07.739 --> 00:52:08.739
What do I get?

00:52:08.739 --> 00:52:09.739
You get your freedom.

00:52:09.739 --> 00:52:11.739
I don't want freedom.

00:52:11.739 --> 00:52:12.739
You know what I want.

00:52:12.739 --> 00:52:14.739
Are we really going to do this again?

00:52:14.739 --> 00:52:15.739
What's the point?

00:52:15.739 --> 00:52:17.739
The point is, you're never home.

00:52:17.739 --> 00:52:19.739
You never spend any time with your family.

00:52:19.739 --> 00:52:22.739
You must be the most self-centered man I know.

00:52:22.739 --> 00:52:23.739
Oh, and I know you.

00:52:23.739 --> 00:52:26.739
Where's the sweet support of girl that I married?

00:52:26.739 --> 00:52:29.739
Whatever happened to reaching out and getting baptized.

00:52:29.739 --> 00:52:31.739
Look, I'm not exactly taking it easy.

00:52:31.739 --> 00:52:33.739
I'm trying to support all of this.

00:52:33.739 --> 00:52:34.739
Remember?

00:52:34.739 --> 00:52:35.739
Oh, and there it is.

00:52:35.739 --> 00:52:37.739
The one thing you're still good at.

00:52:37.739 --> 00:52:38.739
Excuses.

00:52:38.739 --> 00:52:40.739
And you wonder why I'm never here.

00:52:40.739 --> 00:52:42.739
This conversation is over.

00:52:42.739 --> 00:52:44.739
That's not all that's over.

00:52:44.739 --> 00:52:45.739
Oh, yeah?

00:52:45.739 --> 00:52:46.739
Yeah.

00:52:46.739 --> 00:53:13.820
Fine.

00:53:13.820 --> 00:53:14.820
Any way you want it.

00:53:14.820 --> 00:53:15.820
I was begging.

00:53:15.820 --> 00:53:17.820
I feel like I'm never seeing her anymore.

00:53:17.820 --> 00:53:22.199
To be honest, I don't see her much anymore either.

00:53:22.199 --> 00:53:23.199
Is she okay?

00:53:23.199 --> 00:53:24.199
I...

00:53:24.199 --> 00:53:29.170
She's going through another rough patch with Zach.

00:53:29.170 --> 00:53:30.170
I'm so sorry.

00:53:30.170 --> 00:53:32.170
I was hoping things were getting better.

00:53:32.170 --> 00:53:34.929
Thank you.

00:53:34.929 --> 00:53:47.139
You were talking, too?

00:53:47.139 --> 00:53:48.139
It was.

00:53:48.139 --> 00:53:50.139
I wanted to ask about Megan.

00:53:50.139 --> 00:53:52.139
I just did.

00:53:52.139 --> 00:53:54.139
It doesn't sound good.

00:53:54.139 --> 00:53:56.139
I know the elders have tried.

00:53:56.139 --> 00:54:00.139
And now it's really up to them to apply Bible principles.

00:54:00.139 --> 00:54:01.139
Yeah.

00:54:01.139 --> 00:54:05.139
Last time I talked to Megan, she said every time they try and talk it into an argument.

00:54:05.139 --> 00:54:07.139
No two people agree on everything.

00:54:07.139 --> 00:54:11.139
But when we disagree, we have to be kind to one another.

00:54:11.139 --> 00:54:14.679
I just hope it's not too late.

00:54:14.679 --> 00:54:18.679
It never is if they're willing to act unselfishly.

00:54:18.679 --> 00:54:20.679
Oh, that's so true.

00:54:20.679 --> 00:54:23.679
I know every marriage goes through some tough times.

00:54:23.679 --> 00:54:29.679
But if we followed Jehovah's example of unselfish love, we always get through it.

00:54:29.679 --> 00:54:31.679
I just wonder if Megan still believes that.

00:54:31.679 --> 00:55:30.150
Look fantastic.

00:55:30.150 --> 00:55:32.460
Thanks.

00:55:32.460 --> 00:55:34.460
So you're not stored in a coffee bar, are you?

00:55:34.460 --> 00:55:35.460
You remember that?

00:55:35.460 --> 00:55:39.460
I have a near-photographic memory for all coffee-related facts.

00:55:39.460 --> 00:55:41.460
So it's a little busy in here.

00:55:41.460 --> 00:55:42.460
You want to go outside?

00:55:42.460 --> 00:55:43.460
Because in fresh air?

00:55:43.460 --> 00:55:44.460
Yeah, sure.

00:55:44.460 --> 00:55:52.059
A place out over there.

00:55:52.059 --> 00:55:56.559
Oh, it's much better out here.

00:55:56.559 --> 00:55:57.559
It's amazing.

00:55:57.559 --> 00:55:58.559
Yeah.

00:55:58.559 --> 00:55:59.559
Pretty view.

00:55:59.559 --> 00:56:03.380
So what do you do, Landon?

00:56:03.380 --> 00:56:05.380
I'm a live counselor.

00:56:05.380 --> 00:56:07.380
Like a psychiatrist.

00:56:07.380 --> 00:56:08.380
You could say that.

00:56:08.380 --> 00:56:13.380
But more specifically, I focus on couples with marrow problems.

00:56:13.380 --> 00:56:14.380
So you're married?

00:56:14.380 --> 00:56:16.380
Divorced, actually.

00:56:16.380 --> 00:56:19.380
Wait, isn't that a little hypocritical?

00:56:19.380 --> 00:56:20.380
Trust me, it's not.

00:56:20.380 --> 00:56:23.380
I don't help couples force themselves together.

00:56:23.380 --> 00:56:25.380
I help them to confront their issues.

00:56:25.380 --> 00:56:28.380
And sometimes it's best to say.

00:56:28.380 --> 00:56:31.380
Sometimes it's best to leave.

00:56:31.380 --> 00:56:35.719
So, what category are you in?

00:56:35.719 --> 00:56:38.719
Sorry, just an occupational hazard.

00:56:38.719 --> 00:56:42.719
Honestly, I came here tonight to just forget my problems.

00:56:42.719 --> 00:56:44.719
Ah, that's cool.

00:56:44.719 --> 00:56:45.719
I'm curious, though.

00:56:45.719 --> 00:56:47.719
Did you ever marry anybody I know?

00:56:47.719 --> 00:56:48.719
Invite from school?

00:56:48.719 --> 00:56:50.719
No, he was in my congregation growing up.

00:56:50.719 --> 00:56:51.719
All right.

00:56:51.719 --> 00:56:53.719
You were, uh, Jova's witness.

00:56:53.719 --> 00:56:54.719
Yeah.

00:56:54.719 --> 00:56:55.719
Still?

00:56:55.719 --> 00:56:56.719
Of course.

00:56:56.719 --> 00:56:57.719
Nice.

00:56:57.719 --> 00:56:59.719
We'll make it listen.

00:56:59.719 --> 00:57:01.719
Here's a little bit of free advice.

00:57:01.719 --> 00:57:04.719
Now, granted, I don't know your situation.

00:57:04.719 --> 00:57:08.719
I've seen a lot of couples stay in bad marriages.

00:57:08.719 --> 00:57:11.719
Now, they married on impulse, but then as time goes by,

00:57:11.719 --> 00:57:13.719
they just always have nothing to common.

00:57:13.719 --> 00:57:16.719
Instead of just accepting that, making a clean break,

00:57:16.719 --> 00:57:20.719
you know, they try and stick it out or they try and be known.

00:57:20.719 --> 00:57:22.719
The whole time, they're just drifting emotionally.

00:57:22.719 --> 00:57:23.719
They're just pruning.

00:57:23.719 --> 00:57:24.719
They just stop.

00:57:24.719 --> 00:57:25.719
You don't agree?

00:57:25.719 --> 00:57:29.719
It's just that the Bible says that two shall become one flesh.

00:57:29.719 --> 00:57:34.719
It says that, but you think you're really going to be happy

00:57:34.719 --> 00:57:38.719
taking relationship advice from a book written 2,000 years ago.

00:57:38.719 --> 00:57:41.719
What about trusting your heart?

00:57:41.719 --> 00:57:43.719
And if you look in there,

00:57:43.719 --> 00:57:46.719
you'll realize you haven't found your soulmate yet.

00:57:46.719 --> 00:57:49.719
I don't believe in soulmates landing.

00:57:49.719 --> 00:57:50.719
Really?

00:57:50.719 --> 00:57:53.719
Then why'd you come here tonight?

00:57:53.719 --> 00:57:58.039
Well, when you were ready to deal with this,

00:57:58.039 --> 00:57:59.039
here's my card.

00:57:59.039 --> 00:58:01.800
Go ahead.

00:58:01.800 --> 00:58:05.489
I'll talk to you soon.

00:58:05.489 --> 00:58:27.099
Hey, babe.

00:58:27.099 --> 00:58:30.599
How was your day?

00:58:30.599 --> 00:58:33.079
Yeah?

00:58:33.079 --> 00:58:39.460
Liz?

00:58:39.460 --> 00:58:40.460
You okay?

00:58:40.460 --> 00:58:41.460
Yeah.

00:58:41.460 --> 00:58:43.460
I'm just worried about Megan.

00:58:43.460 --> 00:58:46.960
What's going on?

00:58:46.960 --> 00:58:48.960
She's got off the phone with Ellen,

00:58:48.960 --> 00:58:50.960
and she says Zach moved out again.

00:58:50.960 --> 00:58:59.300
I'm sorry to hear that.

00:58:59.300 --> 00:59:00.300
You tried calling her?

00:59:00.300 --> 00:59:04.159
I tried calling, texting.

00:59:04.159 --> 00:59:07.159
She's not responding.

00:59:07.159 --> 00:59:09.159
What if you just went over there?

00:59:09.159 --> 00:59:12.980
The rest time we talked to it,

00:59:12.980 --> 00:59:15.980
it really didn't go so well.

00:59:15.980 --> 00:59:18.980
I'm sorry, babe.

00:59:18.980 --> 00:59:23.289
Let me see if maybe I can find something that'll help, okay?

00:59:23.289 --> 00:59:50.159
Just reminding me of you

00:59:50.159 --> 00:59:53.159
and made me think how we can help Megan right now.

00:59:53.159 --> 00:59:55.159
It says,

00:59:55.159 --> 00:59:57.159
a true friend shows love at all times

00:59:57.159 --> 01:00:01.159
and is a brother who is born for times of distress.

01:00:02.159 --> 01:00:04.159
Don't you think that's the kind of friendship

01:00:04.159 --> 01:00:05.159
you need right now?

01:00:05.159 --> 01:00:19.500
You used to be injured?

01:00:19.500 --> 01:00:20.500
What is Zach?

01:00:20.500 --> 01:00:21.500
What are you doing here?

01:00:21.500 --> 01:00:23.500
Oh, you don't answer your phone.

01:00:23.500 --> 01:00:24.500
What choice do I have?

01:00:24.500 --> 01:00:26.500
Sorry, I changed my number.

01:00:26.500 --> 01:00:28.500
I haven't had a chance to let everybody know yet.

01:00:28.500 --> 01:00:29.500
It's okay.

01:00:29.500 --> 01:00:30.500
Can I come in?

01:00:30.500 --> 01:00:31.500
Um, yeah.

01:00:31.500 --> 01:00:32.500
I mean, I have a few minutes.

01:00:32.500 --> 01:00:33.500
Perfect.

01:00:33.500 --> 01:00:40.269
She's with my parents today.

01:00:40.269 --> 01:00:42.269
I have an appointment to get to.

01:00:42.269 --> 01:00:45.119
Oh, okay.

01:00:45.119 --> 01:00:48.199
What's all this?

01:00:48.199 --> 01:00:49.199
You don't want to know.

01:00:49.199 --> 01:00:57.650
You have phone numbers, secret papers.

01:00:57.650 --> 01:00:59.650
It's not the Megan I know.

01:00:59.650 --> 01:01:03.650
Megan you knew wouldn't file for divorce either.

01:01:03.650 --> 01:01:06.650
You're getting a divorce?

01:01:06.650 --> 01:01:08.650
It's just the beginning stages, but...

01:01:08.650 --> 01:01:10.650
Megan, this isn't making any sense.

01:01:10.650 --> 01:01:15.239
Is this what Zach wants?

01:01:15.239 --> 01:01:19.239
Look, I'm not going to waste any more of my life being unhappy.

01:01:19.239 --> 01:01:24.260
What about what you'll want?

01:01:24.260 --> 01:01:26.260
You married a man that loves Jehovah.

01:01:26.260 --> 01:01:29.260
You still have our times when we don't see eye to eye.

01:01:29.260 --> 01:01:30.260
But with the Bible's help...

01:01:30.260 --> 01:01:32.260
spare me the sermon, okay?

01:01:32.260 --> 01:01:34.260
You don't get it.

01:01:34.260 --> 01:01:37.260
No, I don't.

01:01:37.260 --> 01:01:39.260
Megan, I care about you.

01:01:39.260 --> 01:01:48.929
I appreciate your concern, but I don't need your help anymore.

01:01:48.929 --> 01:01:50.929
I'm helping myself.

01:01:50.929 --> 01:01:53.929
So if you don't mind, I have an appointment to get to.

01:01:53.929 --> 01:02:32.090
Megan.

01:02:32.090 --> 01:02:33.090
Dad?

01:02:33.090 --> 01:02:35.090
What are you doing here?

01:02:35.090 --> 01:02:37.090
I'm looking for you.

01:02:37.090 --> 01:02:38.090
Mom told you.

01:02:38.090 --> 01:02:40.090
I told her not to say anything.

01:02:40.090 --> 01:02:41.090
You shouldn't even be here.

01:02:41.090 --> 01:02:42.090
I'm already late.

01:02:42.090 --> 01:02:43.090
Megan.

01:02:43.090 --> 01:03:15.199
How many times is it going to happen?

01:03:15.199 --> 01:03:16.199
How many times is it going to happen?

01:03:16.199 --> 01:03:17.199
Do you want me to eat garbage?

01:03:17.199 --> 01:03:18.199
Do you want the clients to eat garbage?

01:03:18.199 --> 01:03:19.199
I didn't think so.

01:03:19.199 --> 01:03:20.199
So get it right.

01:03:20.199 --> 01:03:21.199
Excuse me, I'll be back in a second.

01:03:21.199 --> 01:03:25.500
Okay.

01:03:25.500 --> 01:03:30.119
You okay?

01:03:30.119 --> 01:03:31.119
Look, I'm just tired, okay?

01:03:31.119 --> 01:03:32.119
I'll be fine.

01:03:32.119 --> 01:03:33.119
Come on, talk to me.

01:03:33.119 --> 01:03:35.119
Everything okay at home?

01:03:35.119 --> 01:03:37.429
Things are great at home.

01:03:37.429 --> 01:03:38.429
Come on.

01:03:38.429 --> 01:03:40.429
Why don't you tell me what's going on?

01:03:40.429 --> 01:03:42.429
You wouldn't understand.

01:03:42.429 --> 01:03:43.429
Try me.

01:03:43.429 --> 01:03:47.860
We're getting a divorce, okay?

01:03:47.860 --> 01:03:50.269
What?

01:03:50.269 --> 01:03:51.269
Witnesses don't get divorced.

01:03:51.269 --> 01:03:52.269
You told me that.

01:03:52.269 --> 01:03:54.269
Look, it's something that she wants.

01:03:54.269 --> 01:03:56.269
All right.

01:03:56.269 --> 01:03:58.269
What about you?

01:03:58.269 --> 01:03:59.269
What do you want?

01:03:59.269 --> 01:04:04.429
I don't even know anymore.

01:04:04.429 --> 01:04:10.489
Peace.

01:04:10.489 --> 01:04:15.280
I just want some peace in my life.

01:04:15.280 --> 01:04:19.280
Look, obviously, I'm no marriage counselor.

01:04:19.280 --> 01:04:21.280
But I've known you a long time.

01:04:21.280 --> 01:04:23.280
And I've seen what happens when you.

01:04:23.280 --> 01:04:25.280
When you work hard, you know?

01:04:25.280 --> 01:04:28.280
You work hard and things go well.

01:04:28.280 --> 01:04:29.280
What are you talking about?

01:04:29.280 --> 01:04:30.280
I guess what I'm trying to say.

01:04:30.280 --> 01:04:32.280
Does it make sense?

01:04:32.280 --> 01:04:36.280
If you work harder on your marriage?

01:04:36.280 --> 01:04:38.280
Is that something they'd say at those meetings

01:04:38.280 --> 01:04:42.980
or something you read in the Bible or something like that?

01:04:42.980 --> 01:04:43.980
Are you kidding me?

01:04:43.980 --> 01:04:45.980
You're taking sides with the Bible now?

01:04:45.980 --> 01:04:49.980
You're the same guy that told me to focus on this place.

01:04:49.980 --> 01:04:51.980
I did tell you to focus on this place.

01:04:51.980 --> 01:04:53.980
And maybe that was a mistake.

01:04:53.980 --> 01:04:56.980
As your friend, you just seemed happier

01:04:56.980 --> 01:04:58.980
when you were going to those meetings.

01:04:58.980 --> 01:05:00.980
I mean, does that make sense?

01:05:00.980 --> 01:05:01.980
We are done here.

01:05:01.980 --> 01:05:02.980
Why?

01:05:02.980 --> 01:05:03.980
I'm just trying to help you out.

01:05:03.980 --> 01:05:18.340
Oh, I forgot how beautiful it is around here.

01:05:18.340 --> 01:05:20.340
It just seems smaller now.

01:05:20.340 --> 01:05:23.340
You were only seven last time we were here back.

01:05:23.340 --> 01:05:26.340
Yeah, I wish I could go back.

01:05:26.340 --> 01:05:38.039
I didn't come here to say I told you so.

01:05:38.039 --> 01:05:41.039
And I'm not here to judge you.

01:05:41.039 --> 01:05:44.039
So you came here to change my mind.

01:05:44.039 --> 01:05:47.039
Sweetie, you're not seven anymore.

01:05:47.039 --> 01:05:49.039
You have to make your own choices.

01:05:49.039 --> 01:05:50.039
That's right.

01:05:50.039 --> 01:05:52.039
I'm choosing to be happy.

01:05:52.039 --> 01:05:54.039
I made plenty of mistakes.

01:05:54.039 --> 01:05:57.039
But I'm ready to move on.

01:05:57.039 --> 01:06:00.039
And you think this divorce is going to help you move on?

01:06:00.039 --> 01:06:01.039
Yes.

01:06:01.039 --> 01:06:05.320
I didn't set the best example spiritually.

01:06:05.320 --> 01:06:08.320
I didn't take the lead like I should have.

01:06:08.320 --> 01:06:10.320
And I'm really sorry for that.

01:06:11.320 --> 01:06:13.320
No, Megan.

01:06:13.320 --> 01:06:18.320
I've been doing a lot of praying about your mother and me.

01:06:18.320 --> 01:06:20.320
About you.

01:06:20.320 --> 01:06:24.320
I've decided I need to do better spiritually.

01:06:24.320 --> 01:06:26.320
So I'm starting now.

01:06:26.320 --> 01:06:28.320
I don't think I understand.

01:06:28.320 --> 01:06:30.320
What do you mean?

01:06:30.320 --> 01:06:33.320
Before you go through with this divorce.

01:06:33.320 --> 01:06:36.320
Let me ask you one question.

01:06:36.320 --> 01:06:38.320
What is it that brought you to this moment?

01:06:38.320 --> 01:06:41.860
I don't know.

01:06:41.860 --> 01:06:43.860
I guess Zach wasn't the one.

01:06:43.860 --> 01:06:45.860
No, sweetheart.

01:06:45.860 --> 01:06:47.860
You made a choice.

01:06:47.860 --> 01:06:49.860
You chose Zach.

01:06:49.860 --> 01:06:56.869
And did you include Jehovah in that choice?

01:06:56.869 --> 01:06:58.869
Probably not.

01:06:58.869 --> 01:07:00.869
And now you're unhappy.

01:07:00.869 --> 01:07:02.869
God, I know all this.

01:07:02.869 --> 01:07:03.869
Meg, look.

01:07:03.869 --> 01:07:05.869
Here's the point.

01:07:05.869 --> 01:07:09.869
You're about to make another huge decision.

01:07:09.869 --> 01:07:12.869
And who's not being included in that?

01:07:12.869 --> 01:07:16.869
Sweetheart, happiness is always going to allude you.

01:07:16.869 --> 01:07:19.869
If you keep leading Jehovah out of the picture.

01:07:19.869 --> 01:07:22.869
You just don't get it.

01:07:22.869 --> 01:07:26.719
You'd be surprised, Megan.

01:07:26.719 --> 01:07:28.719
Yeah, I doubt it.

01:07:28.719 --> 01:07:35.119
What do you see when you look at your mother and me?

01:07:35.119 --> 01:07:38.119
You guys love each other.

01:07:38.119 --> 01:07:41.119
We do.

01:07:41.119 --> 01:07:43.119
We do.

01:07:45.119 --> 01:07:47.119
But our marriage is imperfect.

01:07:47.119 --> 01:07:49.119
No marriage is.

01:07:49.119 --> 01:07:53.119
It's made up of two imperfect people.

01:07:53.119 --> 01:07:56.590
A sweetie.

01:07:56.590 --> 01:07:58.590
A love centered on Jehovah.

01:07:58.590 --> 01:08:01.590
It takes those two imperfect halves.

01:08:01.590 --> 01:08:05.409
And makes them one flesh.

01:08:05.409 --> 01:08:08.409
But why do I have to make the sacrifice?

01:08:08.409 --> 01:08:11.239
You made the vow.

01:08:11.239 --> 01:08:18.680
The key loves me anymore.

01:08:18.680 --> 01:08:20.680
Maybe he thinks the same about you.

01:08:20.680 --> 01:08:21.680
Reach out to him.

01:08:21.680 --> 01:08:28.640
Trust him.

01:08:28.640 --> 01:08:31.640
You did come here to change my mind.

01:08:31.640 --> 01:08:46.989
No sweetheart, because I love you.

01:08:46.989 --> 01:08:48.989
Love is patient and kind.

01:08:48.989 --> 01:08:53.779
It's not look for its own interest.

01:08:53.779 --> 01:08:56.779
It does not become provoked.

01:08:56.779 --> 01:08:59.779
It does not keep account of the injury.

01:08:59.779 --> 01:09:03.779
It bears all things, believes all things,

01:09:03.779 --> 01:09:05.779
hopes all things,

01:09:05.779 --> 01:09:07.779
and doors all things.

01:09:07.779 --> 01:09:16.659
Look, I know you don't want me here, okay?

01:09:16.659 --> 01:09:18.659
I just came to get a few things.

01:09:18.659 --> 01:09:19.659
Don't worry.

01:09:19.659 --> 01:09:20.659
I want to talk about that.

01:09:20.659 --> 01:09:21.659
No.

01:09:21.659 --> 01:09:23.659
Save it, okay?

01:09:23.659 --> 01:09:30.810
I'm tired of this.

01:09:30.810 --> 01:09:31.810
Never fails.

01:09:31.810 --> 01:09:40.460
Zack.

01:09:40.460 --> 01:09:44.250
Why can't you just leave it alone?

01:09:44.250 --> 01:09:45.250
I'm sick of this, Megan.

01:09:45.250 --> 01:09:47.250
Zack, I just want to talk to you, please.

01:09:47.250 --> 01:09:49.250
You may tell me more things I'm not doing.

01:09:49.250 --> 01:09:51.250
How long are we going to do this?

01:09:51.250 --> 01:09:56.829
No.

01:09:56.829 --> 01:09:58.829
I don't.

01:09:58.829 --> 01:09:59.829
It was a mistake.

01:09:59.829 --> 01:10:01.829
You said so yourself.

01:10:01.829 --> 01:10:05.289
Which one is it, Megan?

01:10:05.289 --> 01:10:06.289
Huh?

01:10:06.289 --> 01:10:07.289
Make up your mind.

01:10:07.289 --> 01:10:16.899
I was wrong.

01:10:16.899 --> 01:10:19.949
Got a good father.

01:10:19.949 --> 01:10:20.949
I'm not a good husband.

01:10:21.949 --> 01:10:23.949
And I never did get baptized.

01:10:23.949 --> 01:10:26.949
So there, you win.

01:10:26.949 --> 01:10:30.949
The only thing I was ever good at was making excuses.

01:10:30.949 --> 01:10:32.949
So why don't you just leave?

01:10:32.949 --> 01:10:43.279
Did you just hear what I said?

01:10:43.279 --> 01:10:54.850
But why would you want to stay with me?

01:10:54.850 --> 01:11:58.590
Instead, I'm trying hard to apply Bible principles.

01:11:58.590 --> 01:12:02.590
I don't know if Zack will ever make the truth his own.

01:12:02.590 --> 01:12:04.590
But with Jehovah's help,

01:12:04.590 --> 01:12:06.590
I'll make it through.

01:12:07.590 --> 01:12:10.590
Thanks for never giving up on me.

01:12:10.590 --> 01:12:12.590
That's fantastic.

01:12:12.590 --> 01:12:27.850
He decided to stop by Paul and Priscilla's one last time

01:12:27.850 --> 01:12:28.850
before our trip.

01:12:28.850 --> 01:12:31.850
They were so excited for us.

01:12:31.850 --> 01:12:34.850
It was hard to believe that after all these years,

01:12:34.850 --> 01:12:37.850
we had finally been accepted to Kingdom Evangelizer School.

01:12:37.850 --> 01:12:42.420
The fields have been an inspiration to me.

01:12:42.420 --> 01:12:44.420
A true love can be found

01:12:44.420 --> 01:12:47.420
if we put Jehovah and his principles first in our life.

01:12:48.420 --> 01:12:50.420
True love is enduring

01:12:50.420 --> 01:12:53.420
and can be enjoyed for all eternity.

01:12:53.420 --> 01:12:56.420
And in the end, Priscilla was right.

01:12:56.420 --> 01:13:00.420
Now I am starting a whole new chapter in my life.
